My quest for [The Artifact] has been a long and treacherous journey fraught with peril. Legend says The Artifact holds power beyond imagination that must be kept safe. Once again the world looks to the Hero to the Downtrodden, Vanquisher of Evil and Defender of Justice.
Return all the Orphans to the Mayor

I'll locate every one of those [Orphans], and gently stuff them into this convenient [Orphan Bag] the Mayor gave me. I'll search high and low until I gather every last one of those cute, yet disgusting, Orphans. I can't help but feel they are my ticket into Lord Von Prong's Castle.

The [Nun] who has been corrupted by the evil of the [Thong of Compassion] can be found up at the [Sanctuary] in the [Dark Forest]. I need to kill her in a spray of justice and return her Thong to Sandy.

I need to find a way to get into the [Catacombs] inside the [Sanctuary] to get to that evil [Nun]. I should pay close attention to what these monks do to get in... maybe I could do the same thing as long as it doesn't involve self-flagellation.

The [Thong of Cuisine] has corrupted a famous chef who wears it, so I'll need to kill her and return the Thong to Sandy. Legend says there is a great chef who lives out west. Legend also says that the pyramids were built by aliens, so you know legends can be trusted.

To become an employee and get access to Wortten and her [Thong of Cuisine], I have to dress up like one of these idiots and show the Receptionist in the T.G.I.W. Factory. Where would I find a [T.G.I.W. Vest] that would also involve killing stuff. Oh yeah, I also need six pieces of silly flair. This is sounding less and less heroic every second.

Getting Wortten's [Thong of Cuisine] involves me passing a drug test to become an employee. This sounds easy because, kids, heroes don't do drugs. The [Drug Testing Machine] is inside the [T.G.I.W. Factory].

The [Thong of Cuisine] worn by Wortten is so close I can taste it. I just need to learn the company [Birthday Song] and sing it to the T.G.I.W. Factory Receptionist to become an employee and get to Wortten. Only way to learn this heroic song of birthdays is to visit a [T.G.I.W's Franchise].

Santa Claus has been corrupted by the [Thong of Generosity] and it's up to the vanquisher of evil to defeat the Jolly Man and recover his Thong for Sandy. His lair is in the frozen wastelands of the sea. I'm pretty sure I know what ''list'' I'll be on after this.
Find a way to Muffle Santa's Mirth
Curse that Jolly Man for throwing me into his dungeon. If I am to defeat the fat, old elf, I will need to find a way to mute the effects of his [Sonic Mirth].
Find Gun Parts for the Army General

Wounded soldiers keep getting their weapons stolen while they're recovering at the [Sanctuary] in the [Dark Forest]. I need to find the missing [Gun Parts] and return them to the General in Le Beaux Kuckelle if the invasion of the North Pole is going to be successful. Santa will never see it coming.

The General in Le Beaux Kuckelle needs some [Gold] for victory medals before the invasion can begin. This general is really thinking ahead. I'll have to keep my heroic eyes and ears wide open for any mention of the precious metal. This is a quest I can really put my heart into.
Fill Out a Map of the North Pole

I need to find a [Ship] and sail around the [North Pole] to map out Santa Claus' island defenses so the Army General in Le Beaux Kuckelle can launch his invasion and I can kill Santa. Wow, I never thought I'd ever say something like that.
Get a Lemon for Captain Taint

Captain Taint down in Scurvyville says I need a [Lemon] to prevent scurvy, so I should probably look for one on a [Farm]. Of course, I'd rather have a lemon meringue pie, but that's not very ''piratey'' and I really need to borrow his [Pirate Ship].

Captain Taint down in Scurvyville says I need [Rum] before I can borrow his [Pirate Ship] to scout the [North Pole]. I guess a drunk crew is a happy crew. I need to find some place that sells spirits of the distilled nature. I hear there is a place in the town of [Strumfuquel].
Get Boat Keys for Captain Taint

Apparently [Plaid Pete] has stolen the [Pirate Ship Keys] to Captain Taint's ship. I have to pay Plaid Pete a visit in his hideout to see if I can convince him to give me the keys, and by convince I mean beat him with my sword.
Get a Liquor License for Grimtub

Before Grimtub Hobblepotty can sell me some [Rum] in his Haunted Crotch Bar in Strumfuquel, I need to return his stolen [Liquor License]. Sounds like it might be hidden in [Wortten's Factory] farther out west.

Madame Primp in Strumfuquel says she doesn't have an opening that can be filled, but I find that hard to believe. She also said that servicemen get preferential treatment. I wish there was some way to prove the [Army General] made me an honorary private.
Deliver the package to the General

I have to take this [Package for the Army General] to some general hanging out at a military base of some sort up north. Being an [Army General] sounds heroic. I bet he has a very heroic sounding name, kind of like DeathSpank.
Deliver the package to the Sheriff of Strumfuquel
Sandy's making me deliver ANOTHER [Package for the Sheriff] over in a town called [Strumfuquel]. What kind of a name is Strumfuquel, anyway?
Deliver the package to the Thong Researcher
I need to give this [Package for the Thongolith Researcher] to... well, to the [Thongolith Researcher]. I'm pretty sure I've seen him somewhere before.

Sandy told me to meet her at her [Secret Base]. I have no idea where it is, which makes sense considering it's ''secret''. The only clue she gave me was this cute [Miniature Thongolith]. I have no idea what to do with this. None. Nadda. Zip. Clueless.
Get a reading of the Thongolith of Compassion

I have to get to the [Thongolith of Compassion] in the [Jungle] and take a reading with the [Thongolith Instrument]. I just need to drop it on the ground for a few seconds, and it'll do the rest. And if I ever lose it, I can get a new one from the Thong Researcher at the Jungle entrance.
Get a reading of the Thongolith of Cuisine

I have to get to the [Thongolith of Cuisine] in the [Cactus Forest] and take a reading with the [Thongolith Instrument]. I just need to drop it on the ground for a few seconds, and it'll do the rest. And if I ever lose it, I can get a new one from the Thong Researcher in Strumfuquel.
Get a reading of the Thongolith of Generosity

I have to get to the [Thongolith of Generosity] on the [North Pole] and take a reading with the [Thongolith Instrument]. I just need to drop it on the ground for a few seconds, and it'll do the rest. And if I ever lose it, I can get a new one from the Thong Researcher on the North Pole Beach.

I need to deliver this [Nitroglycerin] for the Engineer so they can clear some rocks blocking the railroad tracks. This stuff is volatile, so I'll have to be careful. The slightest bump and this whole quadrant is gone. I'll head up the tracks with heroic haste and look for the [Conductor].

I need to destroy the [Mega Bomb] with this [Bazooka] to rid the bridge of Orques so I can get to town and deliver the [Battle Plan Pouch] to the Army General. ''Destroy'' and ''Mega Bomb'' in the same sentence, it's shaping up to be a good day.
I need to follow the dirt path to the west and find the [Orque Comm Tower], and then let the Outpost Soldier know where it is. Sounds too simple for a hero of my caliber. I should get a new agent.
I need to run this [Lit Stick of Dynamite] over to the [Orque Comm Tower] and destroy it for one of the Soldiers who doesn't seem to trust me with a match.

I need to head west of the blown up [Orque Comm Tower] and kill [Colonel Orque] to collect the [Battle Plans] for that Soldier. At least I'm getting to kill stuff now, not that blowing stuff up isn't also fun.
I need to talk to the [Oracle] again, to find the new location of [The Artifact].
I have to deliver this copy of [Magnate Magazine] to [Derek Oil] to rub in the fact that Rich Cabin is the richest man in the land.
I have to deliver this copy of [Landowner Times] to [Derek Oil] to prove that Rich Cabin owns more land than he does.
I have to deliver this copy of [Plutocrat Observer] to [Derek Oil] to rub in the fact that Rich Cabin now has more senators in his back pocket.
I have to deliver this copy of [The Boss Magazine] to [Derek Oil] to further rub in the fact that Rich Cabin has been named ''The Boss.''
I need to kill the [Greem Queen] in the [Jungle] and recover the [Queen Greem Sack] and give it to the Greem Exterminator who's at the north end of the Destroyed City.
Kill the High Plains Greem Queen
I need to kill the [Greem Queen] in the [High Plains] and recover the [Queen Greem Sack] and give it to the Greem Exterminator who's at the north end of the Destroyed City.
I need to kill the [Greem Queen] on [Greem Island] and recover the [Queen Greem Sack] and give it to the Greem Exterminator back in Strumfuquel.
I need to get [Jungle Donkey Manure] for Strunken McClure who lives just to the west of the Destroyed City, to help him grow his crops.
Now I need to get [Dinosaur Manure] from a [Tyrannoraptor] for Strunken, the farmer who lives just to the west of the Destroyed City, to help him grow his crops.
I need to get [Frost Manure] for Strunken, to help him grow his crops. He sure is a needy farmer... but aren't they all.
Throw a Coin down the Well
Whenever I find [Wishing Coins], I should return to the [Talking Well] in the Dark Forest and throw them in for a reward.
From One Law Man to Another
The Stagecoach Driver needs me to deliver a message to the [Sheriff] of the town of [Strumfuquel], just to the west.
I need to kill the [White Rock Bandito Orques] in their camp to the north and return the [Mail Bags] to the Stagecoach Driver.
Get White Bandito Boss' Pearl Hand
I need to kill the [White Rock Bandito Orque Chief] and take his [Pearl Hand] back to the Stagecoach Driver.
The Stagecoach Driver wants me to kill the [Red Renegade Bandito Orques] and return his [Stagecoach Wheels] to him.
The Stagecoach Driver wants me to kill the [Blue Basin Bandito Orques] and recover his [Stagecoach]. They went off towards the [Sandy Desert].
